label.value: Mycobacterium tuberculosis intrinsic murA conferring resistance to fosfomycin

value.value: Mycobacterium tuberculosis murA confers intrinsic resistance to fosfomycin. The presence of an aspartic acid residue in place of the critical cysteine at position 117 that enables fosfomycin binding is believed to be responsible for this intrinsic resistance.

label.value: Chlamydia trachomatis intrinsic murA conferring resistance to fosfomycin

value.value: Chlamydia murA confers intrinsic resistance to fosfomycin. The presence of an aspartic acid residue in place of the critical cysteine at position 119 that enables fosfomycin binding is believed to be responsible for this intrinsic resistance.

definition.value: Inherent parC resistance to fluoroquinolone from an antibiotic producer. The presence of these genes confers self-resistance to the antibiotic it produces.
Inherent ParY resistant to aminocoumarin from an antibiotic producer. The presence of these genes confers self resistance to the antibiotic it produces.

label.value: Bacillus subtilis pgsA with mutation conferring resistance to daptomycin

value.value: Point mutations that occur within the Bacillus subtilis pgsA gene resulting in resistance to daptomycin.

label.value: Campylobacter jejuni gyrA conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones

value.value: Campylobacter jejuni is a major bacterial infectious agent associated with gastroenteritis. Quinolone resistance is reportedly conferred by a single C-257-T nucleotide substitution in the gyrA gene.

label.value: Enterococcus faecium liaF mutant conferring daptomycin resistance

value.value: liaF is an accessory protein that acts as a negative regulator of liaRS signal transduction pathway. Mutations confer daptomycin resistance.

label.value: Enterococcus faecalis liaS mutant conferring daptomycin resistance

value.value: liaS is a histidine kinase found in the liaFSR signal transduction pathway. Mutations confer daptomycin resistance.

label.value: Enterococcus faecalis liaR mutant conferring daptomycin resistance

value.value: liaR is a response regulator found in the liaFSR signal transduction pathway. Mutations confer daptomycin resistance.

Plasmid-mediated SPM metallo-beta-lactamase conferring resistance to carbapenem. Originally isolated from Pseudomonas aeruginosa. Responsible for carbapenem-resistant Pseudomonas aeruginosa (CRPA) outbreaks in Brazil.

label.value: Staphylococcus aureus walK with mutation conferring resistance to daptomycin

value.value: walK is the histidine kinase sensor of a two-component regulatory system controlling peptidoglycan metabolism through regulation of the expression of most of the peptidoglycan hydrolase genes. Mutations in the gene have been found that confer daptomycin resistance.
Mutations to the walK gene, part of a cell wall metabolism 2-component regulatory system, confers resistance to antibiotics, specifically daptomycin.
A class C beta-lactamase found in Acinetobacter baumannii that confers resistance to piperacillin and cefepime.

label.value: Enterococcus faecalis YybT with mutation conferring daptomycin resistance

value.value: YybT has phosphodiesterase activity towards cyclic dinucleotides using a c-di-GMP hydrolyzing phosphodiesterase domain. Mutations to the gene confer resistance to daptomycin.
Mutations to the YybT gene confers daptomycin resistance.

label.value: Enterococcus faecalis gdpD with mutation conferring daptomycin resistance

value.value: gdpD is a glycerolphosphodiesterase whose mutations confer resistance to daptomycin.

Transmembrane protein which expels bicyclomycin from the cell, leading to bicyclomycin resistance. Identified in Pseudomonas aeruginosa strains responsible for outbreaks in Brazil, often appearing with blaSPM-1, another bicyclomycin resistance gene.
Mutations to the gdpD glycerolphosphodiesterase confer resistance to daptomycin.

label.value: Staphylococcus aureus agrA with mutation conferring resistance to daptomycin

value.value: agrA is an autoinducer in a peptide-quorum two-component regulatory system whose mutations confer daptomycin resistance.
Mutations to the regulatory gene agrA confer daptomycin resistance.

label.value: Enterococcus faecalis gshF with mutation conferring daptomycin resistance

value.value: gshF is a bifunctional glutamate-cysteine ligase/ glutathione synthetase that when mutated, confers daptomycin resistance.
Mutations to the glutathione synthetase gshF confers daptomycin resistance.

label.value: Escherichia coli AcrAB-TolC with AcrR mutation conferring resistance to ciprofloxacin, tetracycline, and ceftazidime

value.value: AcrR is a repressor of the AcrAB-TolC multidrug efflux complex. AcrR mutations result in high level antibiotic resistance. The mutations associated with this model are specific to E. coli.

carO is a transmembrane beta-barrel involved in the influx of carbapenem antibiotics in Acinetobacter baumannii. Disruption of the carO gene by distinct insertion elements results in a loss of carO expression causing resistance to carbapenem antibiotics. Homologs of carO have been identified in genera Acinetobacter, Moraxella and Psychrobacter.

label.value: Acinetobacter baumannii OprD conferring resistance to imipenem

value.value: An outer member protein (OMP) found in Acinetobacter baumannii involved in the uptake of imipenem and basic amino acids. This porin is homologous to Pseudomonas aeruginosa OprD, which performs an identical function.
Natural producers of kirromycin and kirromycin-like antibiotics (i.e., kirrothrycin) possess self-resistance, which is classified here.
AdeC is the outer membrane factor of the AdeABC multidrug efflux complex. It can be replaced by other outer membrane channels, and is not essential for antibiotic resistance.

label.value: Enterococcus faecalis drmA with mutation conferring daptomycin resistance

value.value: drmA is an uncharacterized 6-pass membrane protein, with mutations to the protein causing modest resistance to daptomycin.
Mutations to drmA confer daptomycin resistance.

label.value: Enterococcus faecalis YvlB with mutation conferring daptomycin resistance

value.value: YvlB is a putative target of the liaFSR signalling pathway, whose mutations confer daptomycin resistance.
Mutations to the putative liaFSR target YvlB confer daptomycin resistance.

label.value: Acinetobacter baumannii gyrA conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones

value.value: Mutations in the A subunit of DNA gyrase reduce its affinity for fluoroquinolones, thereby conferring resistance.

label.value: Acinetobacter baumannii parC conferring resistance to fluoroquinolones

value.value: Mutations in Acinetobacter baumannii parC that result in resistance to fluoroquinolones.

mgrB is a small transmembrane protein produced in the PhoPQ signalling system. It acts as a negative regulator in this system. Inactivation or down-regulation of mgrB confers colistin resistance by absence as shown in Klebsiella pneumoniae.

BAL30072 is a monocyclic beta-lactam antibiotic belonging to the sulfactams. BAL30072 was found to trigger the spheroplasting and lysis of Escherichia coli rather than the formation of extensive filaments.

Battacin is a cationic lipopeptide antibiotic produced from a Paenibacillus tianmuensis soil isolate. Battacin kills bacteria in vitro and has potent activity against Gram-negative bacteria, including multidrug-resistant and extremely drug-resistant clinical isolates. The bactericidal kinetics of battacin correlate with the depolarization of the cell membrane, suggesting that battacin kills bacteria by disrupting the cytoplasmic membrane.

Benzalkonium chloride is a type of cationic surfactant. It is an organic salt called a quaternary ammonium compound. It has three main categories of use: as a biocide, a cationic surfactant, and as a phase transfer agent.
An alanyl-tRNA synthetase conferring resistance to novobiocin in Escherichia coli. Sequence data unavailable.
Temocillin is a beta-lactamase resistant carboxypenicillin. It is primarily used for the treatment of multiple drug resistant, Gram-negative bacteria, specifically Enterobacteriaceae.

Ticarcillin is a carboxypenicillin used for the treatment of Gram-negative bacteria, particularly P. aeruginosa. Ticarcillin's antibiotic properties arise from its ability to prevent cross-linking of peptidoglycan during cell wall synthesis, when the bacteria try to divide, causing cell death.
Clostridioides difficile and Escherichia coli multidrug efflux transporter with antiporter function. Confers resistance to fluoroquinolones in E. coli and acriflavin in Clostridioides difficile.
qacH is a subunit of the qac multidrug efflux pump in Staphylococcus saprophyticus.

GadW is an AraC-family regulator that promotes mdtEF expression to confer multidrug resistance. GadW inhibits GadX-dependent activation. GadW clearly represses gadX and, in situations where GadX is missing, activates gadA and gadBC.
Mrx is part of the macrolide inactivation gene cluster in Aeromonas hydrophila.
Positive regulator of gene expression in the cysteine regulon. cysB mutants confer resistance to novobiocin, an aminocoumarin antibiotic, in Escherichia coli. Sequence data unavailable.

kdpE is a transcriptional activator that is part of the two-component system KdpD/KdpE that is studied for its regulatory role in potassium transport and has been identified as an adaptive regulator involved in the virulence and intracellular survival of pathogenic bacteria. kdpE regulates a range of virulence loci through direct promoter binding.
MUS-2 is a chromosome-encoded beta-lactamase from Myroides odoratimimus.

leuO, a LysR family transcription factor, exists in a wide variety of bacteria of the family Enterobacteriaceae and is involved in the regulation of as yet unidentified genes affecting the stress response and pathogenesis expression. LeuO is also an activator of the MdtNOP efflux pump.

mfd dissociates transcription elongation complexes blocked at nonpairing lesions and mediates recruitment of DNA repair proteins. The Mfd (mutation frequency decline) protein, also known as transcription-repair coupling factor, is responsible for ATP-dependent removal of stalled RNA polymerase from DNA lesions by inducing forward movement of the RNA polymerase and subsequent recruitment of nucleotide excision repair machinery to the sites of the lesions.

ADC beta-lactamases, also known as AmpC beta-lactamases, are cephalosporinases with extended-spectrum resistance to cephalosporins but not to carbapenems. ADC beta-lactamases are found in Acinetobacter sp. and Oligella urethralis.
